movieData.title: Conclave
movieData.synopsis:
Based on the 2016 novel by Robert Harris, Conclave, is a 2024 mystery thriller directed by Edward Berger, and tells the story of one of the world’s most secretive and ancient events – selecting the new Pope.

After the unexpected death of the Pope, Cardinal-Dean Thomas Lawrence (Ralph Fiennes) is forced to put aside any grief and is tasked with putting together a conclave and running the covert process of selecting a new Pope. Cardinal Lawrence (Fiennes) gathers the Catholic Church’s most powerful leaders from around the world, including the US candidate Bellini (Stanley Tucci), Tedesco (Sergio Castellitto), a more traditional Italian. A more powerful American, Tremblay (John Lithgow), the increasingly popular Nigerian Adeyemi (Lucian Msamati) and the mysterious contender Benitez (Carlos Diehz), who has been working in Kabul. 

However, once they are all locked together in the halls of the Vatican, Lawrence (Fiennes) uncovers a trail of deep secrets which could shake the foundations of the Roman Catholic Church. Conclave stars Ralph Fiennes, Isabella Rossellini, Stanley Tucci, John Lithgow, and Sergio Castellitto.

movieData.title: Exhibition on Screen: Michelangelo Love and Death
movieData.synopsis:
The spectacular sculptures and paintings of Michelangelo seem so familiar to us, but what do we really know about this Renaissance giant? Michelangelo’s genius is evident in everything he touched. Beautiful and diverse works such as the towering statue of David, the moving Pietà in the Papal Basilica of St. Peter and his tour-de-force, the Sistine Chapel ceiling, still leave us breathless today.

Spanning his 88 years, Michelangelo - Love and Death takes a cinematic journey through the print and drawing rooms of Europe through the great chapels and museums of Florence, Rome and the Vatican to seek out a deeper understanding of this legendary figure’s tempestuous life, his relationship with his contemporaries and his incredible legacy.

Through expert commentary, stunning visuals and Michelangelo’s own words, this film takes a fresh look at a master artist whose life and genius are celebrated in every mark he made. Returning to cinemas in 2025 to celebrate this iconic artist’s 550th birthday.

Sculptor, painter, architect, poet, genius - discover why Michelangelo is without a doubt one of the greatest artists of all time.

movieData.title: Exhibition on Screen: The Dawn of Impressionism - Paris, 1874
movieData.synopsis:
The Impressionists are the most popular group in art history - millions flock every year to marvel at their masterpieces. But, to begin with, they were scorned, penniless outsiders. 1874 was the year that changed everything; the first Impressionists, “hungry for independence”, broke the mould by holding their own exhibition outside official channels. Impressionism was born and the art world was changed forever.

What led to that first ground-breaking show 150 years ago? Who were the maverick personalities that wielded their brushes in such a radical and provocative way? The spectacular Musée d’Orsay exhibition brings fresh eyes to this extraordinary tale of passion and rebellion. The story is told not by historians and curators but in the words of those who witnessed the dawn of Impressionism: the artists, press and people of Paris, 1874. See the show that changed everything on the big screen.

Made in close collaboration with the Musee d’Orsay and National Gallery of Art, Washington D.C.

To protect him from Rome's corruption, Lucilla (Connie Nielsen) sent him to Numidia. However, when General Marcus Acacius (Pedro Pascal) invades, Lucius is captured and forced back to the gladiatorial arena.

Acclaimed director Ridley Scott returns, promising the same epic scale that made the original a classic. With fierce battles and political intrigue, Gladiator II is set to honour its predecessor while carving out its own place in cinematic history. Sharpen your swords; the arena awaits once more!

movieData.title: Joker: Folie à Deux
movieData.synopsis:
Joker: Folie à Deux is a musical psychological thriller that plunges even deeper into the chaotic mind of Arthur Fleck, the man who became the Joker. 

Directed by Todd Phillips, this sequel to the critically acclaimed Joker (2019) reintroduces Joaquin Phoenix in his Oscar-winning role as the titular character, now joined by Lady Gaga as Lee, a fellow inmate at Arkham State Hospital. The film explores the twisted romance between these two damaged souls as they embark on a dark and dangerous journey together.

Set two years after the events of the first film, Joker: Folie à Deux finds Arthur Fleck locked away in Arkham after inciting a citywide riot and murdering a talk show host on live television. Within the cold confines of the psychiatric hospital, Arthur meets Lee, a music therapist whose obsession with him—and with the Joker persona—quickly spirals into a delusional and deadly romance. As their bond intensifies, the line between reality and fantasy blurs, and their shared psychosis manifests in musical numbers that range from classic ballads to twisted, hallucinatory show tunes.

The film is a blend of psychological horror and musical spectacle, featuring scenes that echo the vibrant feel of musicals, reimagined through the lens of Arthur’s madness.

movieData.title: Preview: The Sinking of the Lisbon Maru
movieData.originalTitle: Li Si Ben Wan Chen Mo
movieData.synopsis:
The Sinking of the Lisbon Maru is a poignant documentary directed by Fang Li that sheds light on a forgotten chapter of World War II. In October 1942, the Lisbon Maru, a Japanese transport ship secretly carrying over 1,800 British prisoners of war, was torpedoed off the coast of China by an American submarine unaware of its human cargo.

Through rare archival footage, survivor testimonies, and expert interviews, the documentary uncovers the harrowing journey of the prisoners as the ship began to sink, leaving them trapped below deck. The film also highlights local Chinese fishermen who risked their lives to rescue as many prisoners as they could.

movieData.synopsis: At 11:30 pm on October 11th, 1975, a ferocious troupe of young comedians and writers changed television forever. movieData.title: Sky Original - Mussolini: Son of the Century + Live Q&A
movieData.originalTitle: Mussolini: Son of the Century + Live Q&A
movieData.synopsis:
Everyman members are invited to join us for an exclusive preview of Mussolini: Son of the Century, an eight-part Sky Original drama based on Antonio Scurati’s award-winning and internationally bestselling novel.

This series tells the story of the birth of fascism in Italy, tracing Benito Mussolini's rise to power from the founding of the Fasci Italiani in 1919 to his infamous 1925 speech in parliament following the murder of socialist MP Giacomo Matteotti. Delving into Mussolini’s complex personal relationships—his wife Rachele, his lover Margherita Sarfatti, and other iconic figures of the time—while portraying a nation’s descent into dictatorship and the relentless resilience of a man who rose from his ashes time and again.

In Italian with English subtitles – event runtime: 8hrs 30mins

On arrival, you’ll be greeted with complimentary refreshments and the perfect spot on a comfy sofa to settle in for Part 1 of the series (episodes 1-4). Afterwards, there will be an exclusive live Q&A session with the filmmakers and cast, leading into an interval featuring complimentary food and drinks. Following the break, we settle in for Part 2 (episodes 5-8), then end the day with a celebratory drinks reception to toast the series.

Running Order for the Day 1:
13:00 – Arrivals
13:30 – Part 1: Episodes 1–4
17:00 – Live Q&A
17:30 – Interval + Complimentary refreshments
18:15 – Part 2: Episodes 5–8
21:30 – Screening ends + Drink reception

movieData.title: The Metropolitan Opera: Aida
movieData.synopsis: American soprano Angel Blue headlines as the Ethiopian princess torn between love and country in a new production of Verdi’s Aida by Michael Mayer that brings audiences inside the towering pyramids and gilded tombs of ancient Egypt with intricate projections and dazzling animations. Romanian-Hungarian mezzo-soprano Judit Kutasi also stars as Aida’s rival, Amneris, alongside Polish tenor Piotr Beczała as the soldier Radamès—completing opera’s greatest love triangle. Met Music Director Yannick Nézet-Séguin takes the podium to conduct the January 25 performance, which will be broadcast live from the Metropolitan Opera stage to cinemas worldwide.

movieData.title: The Metropolitan Opera: Fidelio
movieData.synopsis: Following a string of awe-inspiring Live in HD performances, Norwegian soprano Lise Davidsen returns to the Metropolitan Opera as Leonore, the faithful wife who risks everything to save her husband from the clutches of tyranny in Beethoven’s Fidelio. Completing the distinguished cast is British tenor David Butt Philip as the political prisoner Florestan, Polish bass-baritone Tomasz Konieczny as the villainous Don Pizarro, veteran German bass René Pape as the jailer Rocco, Chinese soprano Ying Fang and German tenor Magnus Dietrich as the young Marzelline and Jaquino, and Danish bass Stephen Milling as the principled Don Fernando. Susanna Mälkki conducts the March 15 performance, which will be broadcast live from the Met stage to cinemas worldwide.

movieData.synopsis: The Metropolitan Opera’s 2024–25 Live in HD season comes to a close with a live broadcast of Rossini’s effervescent comedy on May 31. Russian mezzo-soprano Aigul Akhmetshina headlines a winning ensemble as the feisty heroine, Rosina, alongside American tenor Jack Swanson, in his Met debut, as her secret beloved, Count Almaviva. Moldovan baritone Andrey Zhilikhovsky stars as Figaro, the ingenious barber of Seville, with Hungarian bass-baritone Peter Kálmán as Dr. Bartolo and Russian bass Alexander Vinogradov as Don Basilio rounding out the principal cast. Giacomo Sagripanti conducts Bartlett Sher’s madcap production.

movieData.synopsis: Experience the ninth season of the Metropolitan Opera's Peabody and Emmy Award-winning series The Met: Live in HD in select cinemas nationwide. movieData.title: The Metropolitan Opera: Salome
movieData.synopsis: Met Music Director Yannick Nézet-Séguin takes the podium on May 17 to conduct Strauss’s one-act tragedy, which will be broadcast live from the Metropolitan Opera stage to cinemas worldwide. Leading the company’s first new production of the work in 20 years, Claus Guth, one of Europe’s leading opera directors, gives the biblical story a psychologically perceptive Victorian-era setting. South African soprano Elza van den Heever leads a celebrated cast as the abused and unhinged antiheroine, with Swedish baritone Peter Mattei as the imprisoned prophet Jochanaan; German tenor Gerhard Siegel as Salome’s lecherous stepfather, King Herod; American mezzo-soprano Michelle DeYoung as his wife, Herodias; and Polish tenor Piotr Buszewski as Narraboth.

movieData.title: The Room Next Door
movieData.synopsis:
In The Room Next Door, acclaimed writer Ingrid (Julianne Moore) reconnects with her estranged friend Martha (Tilda Swinton), a terminally ill war journalist, who invites her to be present during her final days.

Directed by Pedro Almodóvar in his first English-language film, this adaptation of Sigrid Nunez’s novel 'What Are You Going Through' explores the deep, complicated bonds of friendship and the inevitability of death. 

Set in an upstate New York house, the story follows Ingrid as she grapples with Martha’s decision to end her life on her own terms, using a euthanasia pill. With nuanced performances from Moore and Swinton, the film resonates as a meditation on death, love, and the enduring connections between people, even in the face of life’s end.
movieData.advisory: infrequent strong language, drug misuse, moderate threat, upsetting scenes

In Trap, directed by twist master M. Night Shyamalan, Josh Hartnett stars as a father who takes his teenage daughter (Ariel Donoghue) to a seemingly innocent pop concert. movieData.title: Wicked
movieData.synopsis:
Wicked is the highly anticipated prequel to The Wizard of Oz, based on the hit Broadway musical by Stephen Schwartz and Winnie Holzman. 

This epic fantasy tells the untold story of two iconic figures—Elphaba (Cynthia Erivo), a misunderstood young woman born with green skin, and Glinda (Ariana Grande), a popular, ambitious student. Set at Shiz University, the film follows their unlikely friendship as they navigate prejudice, power, and the dark political forces in the Land of Oz. While Glinda basks in privilege, Elphaba’s defiance of the Wizard (Jeff Goldblum) leads her down a path that transforms her into the Wicked Witch of the West. As their lives take opposing directions, their choices ripple across Oz, forever altering its future.

Featuring stunning performances and iconic music, Wicked delivers a reimagined origin story of the witches of Oz, challenging what it truly means to be “Wicked.”
